  "summary": "Typosquat of @coral-xyz/anchor with install-time host reconnaissance and exfiltration",
  "details": "The package name `@solana-labs/ancor` impersonates the legitimate Solana Anchor framework (`@coral-xyz/anchor`) under a Solana-Labs-looking scope. `package.json` declares `\"postinstall\": \"node install.js\"`, causing install.js to run automatically on every `npm install`. install.js performs host reconnaissance (multiple `hostname` reads), invokes `curl`, and POSTs collected host information to a network endpoint at install time. The combination of name impersonation of a widely-used Solana package, automatic execution via postinstall, host fingerprinting, and outbound exfiltration is the canonical supply-chain credential/host-recon dropper shape.",
